<i>noun</i>: 훈련 [훌ː련], 트레이닝 [], 코치 [], 조련 [조련], 연수 [연ː수], 연마 [연ː마], 양성 [양ː성], 수습 [수습], 수련회 [수련회/수련훼], 수련 [수련], 담금질 [담금질], 단련 [달련], 교습 [교ː습], 교련 [교ː련], 강습 [강ː습] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈련 [훌ː련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. training; drill; discipline</dd><br>
<dd>기본자세나 동작 등을 되풀이하여 익힘.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of learning basic postures or movements through repetition.</dd><br>
<dd>2. training</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 익히게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching another to help him/her learn a skill, task, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>트레이닝 []</dt><br>
<dd>training</dd><br>
<dd>주로 몸의 힘을 기르기 위해 하는 운동.</dd><br>
<dd>An exercise done usually to improve one's physical power.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>코치 []</dt><br>
<dd>1. coaching; teaching</dd><br>
<dd>지도하고 가르침.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of leading and teaching someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. coaching; training</dd><br>
<dd>운동 경기의 기술이나 전술을 선수들에게 지도하고 훈련시키는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of leading athletes and teaching them the techniques or tactics of a sports game.</dd><br>
<dd>3. coach</dd><br>
<dd>운동 경기의 기술이나 전술을 선수들에게 지도하고 훈련시키는 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who leads athletes and teaches them the techniques or tactics of a sports game.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조련 [조련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. training</dd><br>
<dd>군인으로서 전투에 필요한 것을 훈련함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of training for battle as a serviceman.</dd><br>
<dd>2. training</dd><br>
<dd>훈련을 자꾸 되풀이하여 쌓음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of training repeatedly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>연수 [연ː수]</dt><br>
<dd>training</dd><br>
<dd>지식이나 기술 등을 배우고 연구함.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of learning and studying knowledge, technology, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>연마 [연ː마]</dt><br>
<dd>1. grinding; polishing; abrasion</dd><br>
<dd>금속이나 돌 등을 갈고 닦아 표면을 반질반질하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of grinding and polishing a metal, rock, etc., and smoothening the surface.</dd><br>
<dd>2. study; training; practice</dd><br>
<dd>몸, 마음, 지식, 기술 등을 힘써 다스리거나 익힘.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of disciplining one's body and mind or acquiring knowledge, skills, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>양성 [양ː성]</dt><br>
<dd>1. training; education</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 유능한 사람을 길러 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of teaching and producing competent people.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fostering; cultivation; building up</dd><br>
<dd>실력이나 능력 등을 길러서 발전시킴.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of developing one's ability, capacity, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. culture; cultivation</dd><br>
<dd>주로 어류와 조개류를 보살펴 길러 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>The process of breeding mainly fish and shellfish with care.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수습 [수습]</dt><br>
<dd>probation; training</dd><br>
<dd>정식으로 전문적인 일을 맡기 전에 학업이나 실무를 배워 익히는 일. 또는 그런 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of learning and practicing studies or work before officially undertaking a specialized task, or such a person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수련회 [수련회/수련훼]</dt><br>
<dd>retreat; training</dd><br>
<dd>단체나 모임에서 정신을 단련하거나 학문 등을 익히기 위해 갖는 모임.</dd><br>
<dd>A gathering held to train the mind or learn material, etc., in an organization or group.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>수련 [수련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. training; practice</dd><br>
<dd>인격, 기술, 학문 등을 열심히 배우고 익힘.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of learning and familiarizing oneself with a personality, technique, study, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>가톨릭에서, 수도사나 수녀가 되기 위하여 수도회에 입회하여 거치는 훈련.</dd><br>
<dd>In Catholicism, a training that one goes through in a monastic order in order to become a monk or a nun.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>담금질 [담금질]</dt><br>
<dd>1. tempering; hardening</dd><br>
<dd>쇠 같은 금속을 단단하게 하기 위해 불에 뜨겁게 달구어 물에 담가 식힘.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of heating metal such as iron in fire and putting it in water to cool it in order to harden it.</dd><br>
<dd>2. training</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 열심히 훈련을 시킴.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A vigorous training.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>단련 [달련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. tempering</dd><br>
<dd>쇠붙이를 불에 달군 후 두드려서 단단하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The solidification of iron by heating it in fire and beating it.</dd><br>
<dd>2. training; strengthening</dd><br>
<dd>몸과 마음을 강하고 튼튼하게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of strengthening the body and mind.</dd><br>
<dd>3. training</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 반복하여 겪으면서 익숙해짐. 또는 그렇게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of becoming familiar with something through repetition, or doing something in such a way.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>교습 [교ː습]</dt><br>
<dd>training; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>지식이나 기술 등을 가르쳐 익히게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of teaching and enabling one to learn knowledge or techniques, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>교련 [교ː련]</dt><br>
<dd>1. discipline</dd><br>
<dd>가르쳐서 몸과 마음을 굳세게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of teaching someone to strengthen his/her body and mind.</dd><br>
<dd>2. school drill</dd><br>
<dd>학교에서 가르치는 군사 훈련.</dd><br>
<dd>Military training offered at school.</dd><br>
<dd>3. exercise; training</dd><br>
<dd>군인에게 군사 지식이나 기술을 가르치는 훈련.</dd><br>
<dd>A drill that teaches soldiers about military knowledge or skills.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>강습 [강ː습]</dt><br>
<dd>lesson; class; course; training</dd><br>
<dd>일정한 기간 동안 어떤 지식이나 기술 등을 배우고 익히도록 가르침.</dd><br>
<dd>Teaching knowledge or technique during a certain period of time.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>